      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "STOJANOVIC (4) ran a convincing 22.36 when winning over 400m at Geelong last start. Top win latest and looms as the one to beat again. LEAP OF FAITH (3) was below best last time finishing fourth at this track, but prior to that had been racing well including a Grade 5 H NP win two back at Ballarat. Has the ability and expected to do much better. KRAKEN RIPPER (6) was safely held last time out, finishing eighth at Shepparton over 450m behind Detectable (25.92) in a Grade 5. Scored at his previous run. Still to record a win from this draw but has never missed the frame in two starts. Key runner who gets his chance to atone. RHYTHMIC ENERGY (1) generally performs well over this distance.",
